    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="333"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6231/518: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 24, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Your 10, January 23, noon.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>While desiring that Embassy shall assist American concerns interested in
                        making barter arrangements by facilitating their approach to the proper
                        German authorities, I nevertheless feel that the Embassy should not discuss
                        with the German authorities specific proposals nor intercede with them in
                        support of individual arrangements.</item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>As regards possible discussion with Schacht of the Tariff Commission’s
                        trade analysis for 1932, made under the Costigan resolution, it is felt that
                        it would be inadvisable at this time to enter upon such a discussion.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
